{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p> <a href=\"/light_drum_prototype-1f4a0324b2dbaedf0a9bf3cb365710d9.jpg\"><img src=\"/light_drum_prototype-1f4a0324b2dbaedf0a9bf3cb365710d9.jpg\"></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"/playing_light_drum_prototype-23c86a55726869eb90ee85ec87867efc.jpg\"><img src=\"/playing_light_drum_prototype-23c86a55726869eb90ee85ec87867efc.jpg\"></a></p>\n<p>Since I was like 10, I wanted to make a midi drum pad with infra-red light beams to break instead of pads to hit. Now I've been working with PIC16f84 chips and realized I could do it pretty easily.</p>\n<p>This prototype had two light-pads that sent midi successfully.</p>\n<p>The next step will be to make one with 8 pads and build a usable model to see if that's enough or if I want to multiplex and have 16 or more pads.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/light_drum","title":"Light Drum","date":"2003-04-06","tags":["midi"]}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"prev":{"html":"<h3>Failed downloads:</h3>\n<h3>Failed hexagons:</h3>\n<h3>Hexagons images:</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/light_drum_prototype.jpg_hexagon-c7f1dd135ab840d2daaef6167c65fce3.jpeg\" alt=\"light_drum_prototype.jpg_hexagon.jpeg\">\n<img src=\"/playing_light_drum_prototype.jpg_hexagon-f34bfff9633c7725595efcfd7b129866.jpeg\" alt=\"playing_light_drum_prototype.jpg_hexagon.jpeg\"></p>","id":"6a5a9421-dc56-5d11-be56-6689a8dab33e","frontmatter":{"path":"/light_drum_images","title":"Light Drum (images)","date":"2003-04-06","tags":["midi"],"hexagonImages":null}},"next":{"html":"<h3>Failed downloads:</h3>\n<h3>Failed hexagons:</h3>\n<h3>Hexagons images:</h3>\n<p> <img src=\"/ltrthgz.jpg_hexagon-392f512132ef55ef85f0d1852e25fa82.jpeg\" alt=\"ltrthgz.jpg_hexagon.jpeg\"></p>","id":"9bfa7403-f13b-5c51-8176-a7b667801271","frontmatter":{"path":"/litterthugz_broach_images","title":"Litterthugz Broach (images)","date":"2004-03-21","tags":["beadwork","cna","litterthugz","mike 2600","st-louis"],"hexagonImages":null}}}}